\begin_layout Standard
In this view a sustained period of low inflation will imply that there is a consensus among those individuals and institutions with the power to change or challenge existing relative prices,
 that the existing prices are in some sense fair or normal.
 This does not necessarily mean that most individuals in a low inflationary economy believe that the distribution of income resulting from the prevailing relative prices and wages is fair,
 but rather that those who perceive it to be unfair do not have the power to change prices or wages in their favour.
